rding to official website, the size of Tamer Park is around 17,600 square metres (<a href=\"https://www.lcsd.gov.hk/en/parks/tp/index.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lcsd.gov.hk%2Fen%2Fparks%2Ftp%2Findex.html&d=YBElpbzmALMQinc%2Bu7edP2zUwbN2nhMFbUYjFdDHJd4%3D&h=d42e0f8b\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.lcsd.gov.hk/en/parks/tp/index.html</a>). <br />\n<br />\nAssuming 1 square metres could accommodate 5 persons, the maximum amount of pro- Beijing protestors is around 88,000.<br />\n<br />\nNot to mention there&rsquo;re trees, building structures inside the park so the 165,000 is likely an overestimate.<br />\n<br />\nIt is understood that in your article reads &lsquo;local media says 165,000 protestors turned up....&rsquo; but in your facebook &lsquo;pretext&rsquo; it claims directly an estimated 165,000 protestors turned up.<br />\n<br />\nYour media professionalism is respected but any news reporting that might mislead the world&rsquo;s reader should warrant your close attention.<br />\n<br />\n有冇人有尋日撐警劣行嘅片/相整合 link？"}]}